										<p>India is home to over 15 million visually impaired people, i.e. 50% of the total visually impaired population in the world. Sadly, only 1% of the existing literature is accessible and available to them in the form of audiobooks. To bring literature closer to the visually impaired, it has to happen seamlessly and in the right manner: in the language they understand.  </p>

